-- ADM bids for flavours firm Wild as suitors line up - sources
-- 
-- Fri May 23, 2014 01:42PM EDT
-- None



LONDON/FRANKFURT, May 23 (Reuters) - Leading global agribusiness group Archer Daniels Midland Co <ADM.N> is among the bidders for German drink and food flavours maker Wild in a deal valued at 1.5 billion euros ($2.04 billion), sources familiar with the deal said on Friday.

Illinois-based ADM declined to comment.